## Step 10: Regenerate Command Center Dashboard

After all data updates are complete, regenerate `lumifai/insights/command-center.html`:

1. Read the Excel tracker (all sheets) using openpyxl
2. Convert all data to JSON format matching the `DATA` object structure in the HTML template
3. Embed the JSON into the dashboard HTML template
4. Save to `lumifai/insights/command-center.html`

**Read `references/design-system.md` before generating any HTML.** All HTML outputs must
follow the Lumif.ai design system (warm cream background, Inter font, 3-state badges only,
8px spacing rhythm, minimal shadows).

The dashboard has tabs for: Overview, Expert Calls (searchable/filterable table),
Action Items, Research Queue, ICPs (card view), Competitors, Context Graph (embedded),
and Products. It includes CSV export and print-to-PDF buttons.

**Use the existing HTML template as the base** — only update the `DATA` object with
current tracker contents. Do not rebuild the HTML/CSS/JS from scratch each time.

